::Feline::

She purred softly, "But what about our symbols? Do you have a maximal 
symbol that we may use to over up our own symbols with? Or do we cut 
off our symbols and go without one?"



--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, Yanshosh@a... wrote:
> Don't worry about it, Dcoburn!
> 
> ::Zardus::
> 
> Zardus nods at Skulletron's responce. So far, this was good.
> 
> "No," he says in responce to Feline's question, "Sabotauge would be 
too 
> dangerous. Instead, you two are meerly scanning."
> 
> He looks at the two, wondering if they could pull this off. "You 
two will 
> arrive at the Maximal base, posing as two Maximals."
> 
> Zardus looks at Feline, "You shall use your charm, along with some 
help from 
> Skulletron's abilities, to lure the Maximals into giving you two 
quarters. 
> Once inside, you will scan the ship, and use the computers in your 
quarters 
> to find out as much as you can about it, the defences and 
everything. Get a 
> tour if you can."
> 
> He presses a button on the holo-projector, the hologram 
disapearing. "Then 
> you two get out."
> 
> Zardus looks at Skulletron, "This is where your part really begins. 
On your 
> way out, you shall tamper with the Maximals' emotions. Make them 
mad at each 
> other, or fall in love with different bots."
> 
> He presses another button on the holo-projector, an image of Iron 
Raptor 
> appearing. "This is their leader," he says, pointing to the 
projection, "If 
> you can make them fall in love with her, it would make a good 
amount of 
> trouble between the Maximals. But don't overdo it, if they're 
killing each 
> other in the halls, you'll have trouble getting out."
> 
> Zardus looks at the two bots, "Any questions?"
